         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne, ¶ 31/5/89 ¶ T. R. Wilson Esqr ¶ Under Secretary. ¶ Sir...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">89.05.31</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Thomas Wilson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">N89/6934, unit 501, VPRS 3992/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">31/5/89</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">T. R. Wilson Esqr</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Under Secretary.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In reply to your telegram of yesterday<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Telegram not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I have the honor to inform you, that the printing of the Census of Australian plants, 1000 impressions, cost pr. sheet £11. 7 - and corrections 8/6d. Three tenders were enquired for at the time, and Mess Carron, Bird &amp; Coy<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e. McCarron, Bird &amp; Co.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was the lowest; indeed one firm did not wish to enter on the work on account of the latin names and the peculiar difficulty of setting up the types.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Chief Secretary, A. Deakin, minuted his approval on 6 June 1890 and M was informed immediately. He returned the file 'with best thanks' the next day. Wilson promptly referred it to the Commissioners of Audit who replied on 19 June asking him to 'be good enough to inform us how this expenditure of £250 is to be provided for'. Wilson referred the question to M 'for early report'. M replied on 25 June: 'This expenditure will be met out of the vote for "publication of works on plants" Div. 16, subdivis. 4'. Wilson forwarded the file to the Commissioners of Audit the next day along with calculations reaching £250 based on 20 sheets at £11.5.0 = £220, plus corrections at 8/6 [£8.10.0] totalling £228.10.0. This was rounded off: 'Estimates of cost of new Edition £250.0.0'. The Commissioners of Audit replied on 10 July: 'In view of the fact that tenders for the work were not "publicly invited" as required by clause 67 of the Consolidated General Regulations, we consider the approval of the Governor in Council necessary for the expenditure of the money as proposed'.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On 22 July the Chief Secretary wrote: 'It is recommended for the approval of His Excellency the Administrator of the Government in Council that the undermentioned service be performed without Tenders being advertised for the same viz:— Printing one thousand copies of the "Census of Australian Plants" for the Government Botanist.'</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In M to O. Tepper, 27 July 1889 reported that the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Census</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(B89.12.03) was going through the press.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir, your obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
         </div>
